 EDIT FILE  ✨ CREATE /Users/davidgorham/Documents/Puppy Projects/Bentley App/README.md
+ # Mr. Slicey Butcher Shop
+ 
+ Tiny horror-themed 2D pixel-style web game built with Phaser.
+ 
+ ## Current Build (Vertical Slice)
+ - 3 escalating deliveries
+ - Core loop: **Deliver → get hunted → solve switches/key puzzle → escape**
+ - Chase-survival gameplay with increasing tension each round
+ - Keyboard controls and replay flow
+ 
+ ## Stack
+ - Phaser 3
+ - Vite
+ - JavaScript (ES modules)
+ 
+ ## Run Locally
+ ```bash
+ npm install
+ npm run dev
+ ```
+ Then open the local Vite URL (usually `http://localhost:5173`).
+ 
+ ## Controls
+ - Move: `WASD` or Arrow keys
+ - Sprint: `Shift`
+ - Interact: `E`
+ - Start game: `Space`
+ - Replay from ending: `R`
+ 
+ ## Gameplay Goals
+ 1. Deliver meat at the front counter.
+ 2. Find the freezer key.
+ 3. Activate required power switches.
+ 4. Escape via right-side exit before the hunter catches you.
+ 
+ ## Project Structure
+ ```text
+ src/
+   game/
+     constants.js
+     state.js
+     ui.js
+   scenes/
+     BootScene.js
+     TitleScene.js
+     DeliveryScene.js
+     EndScene.js
+   main.js
+ ```
+ 
+ ## Next Suggested Improvements
+ - Tilemap + real pixel assets (character sprites, props, lighting)
+ - Patrol + line-of-sight hunter AI (instead of direct homing)
+ - Puzzle variety (code lock, crate push room, breaker rerouting)
+ - Audio layer (ambient hum, footsteps, fake-out noises)
+ - Save/checkpoint system and expanded story beats

