 AGENT RESPONSE 
Absolutely — done. 🐶✅
I updated the game so text is in its own section and no longer overlaps gameplay objects.

What I changed
──────────────

1) Dedicated UI section (left panel)
• Added a fixed left UI panel.
• All narrative/objective/hint text now lives there.
• Gameplay area is now separate on the right side.

2) Play area boundaries
• Moved all game objects (player, hunter, crates, switches, key, counter, door) into the right playfield.
• Added movement clamping so player/hunter stay inside that area cleanly.

3) Labels for boxes/door
I added on-map labels so players know what’s what:
• Counter
• Key
• Switch A / Switch B / Switch C
• Exit Door
• Old Man

Also added a small legend in the UI panel:
• Counter = drop delivery
• Key = freezer key item
• Switches = power
• Exit Door = way out
• Player/Hunter color hints

4) Text wrapping fix
• Added word-wrap to title/story/objective/hint text so it stays inside panel width.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

If you want next, I can make the labels smarter (only appear when nearby or after objective unlock) so the horror vibe stays cleaner and less “arcade HUD heavy.”

