Perfect — I juiced the death sound into a proper animatronic-style jump blast. 😈🔊

What I changed
In JumpscareScene I replaced the old simple screech with a layered, nasty original sound design:

• Fast attack white-noise burst (instant panic hit)
• Detuned saw + square lead drop
• Bandpass filtering sweep
• WaveShaper distortion (crunch)
• Low sub drop for body impact
• Short, loud, abrupt envelope (~0.95s total)

So now death feels way more like that FNAF-style “OH NOPE” moment.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

If you want it even more brutal, I can add:
• a randomized pitch variant each death (less repetitive),
• a double-hit stinger (second mini blast 100ms later),
• optional volume slider in settings so it doesn’t annihilate headphones.

