YEAH that’s a great note 😂
I just tuned it from “screech” to way more of that “AAARRRGGGAAAFF” vibe.

What I changed in the jumpscare sound
─────────────────────────────────────

In JumpscareScene.playScreech() I replaced the tone with a more vocal-monster stack:

• Throat growl oscillators (saw + square + triangle)
• Moving formant filters to mimic rough vowel/consonant shape
• Heavy distortion for gnarly rasp
• Noise rasp layer for breath/scream texture
• Low plosive hit up front for that “AARR-” slam

So now it hits more like a guttural roar-bark instead of a pure electronic shriek.

If you want it even more “AAARRGGAAFF,” next tweak is easy:
• longer tail by +0.2s
• lower pitch 10–15%
• extra crackle burst at the end (“-FF”).

