Easy 🐶

How to get your GitHub repo URL
───────────────────────────────

 1. Go to https://github.com
 2. Click + (top right) → New repository
 3. Name it something like: mr-slicey-butcher-shop
 4. Click Create repository
 5. On the next page, you’ll see “Quick setup” with URL options:

HTTPS URL looks like:
https://github.com/YOUR-USERNAME/mr-slicey-butcher-shop.git

SSH URL looks like:
git@github.com:YOUR-USERNAME/mr-slicey-butcher-shop.git

Copy one of those and paste it here.
I’ll push your folder right away.

(If you’re not using SSH keys yet, use HTTPS — easiest.)

